*(Imagined as a direct, data-driven critique — calm but urgent, reflecting his "no 1:1s" preference for group truth-seeking)*  

> **Huang**: *"I respect the TFA’s intent — but let’s stress-test it with NVIDIA’s reality. You say AI must operate within planetary boundaries *today*. Yet our latest Hopper architecture delivers 30x more AI training per watt than predecessors — precisely because we treated energy constraints as *engineering challenges*, not stop signs. Your Biosphere Audits would force us to halt training runs over marginal water-use spikes in Arizona, while ignoring that the *same* AI is optimizing Colorado River allocation to save 200B gallons/year (per our work with SRP).  
