His calm, data-driven approach wouldn’t reject the TFA’s goals — he’d ask: *"If your framework treats the very tool that can solve ecological collapse as a threat to be contained, what future are you actually aligning *to*?"* That question isn’t a challenge to the TFA’s values — it’s a challenge to its *theory of change*.  

