- Bryan Stevenson (anti-dehumanization/narrative justice)

Each critique revealed critical blind spots in the original TFA. The user isn't just asking for minor tweaks - they want a complete rebuild that centers the hard-won wisdom from these lived-experience perspectives.

What strikes me most is how each Earthling exposed a different dimension of what "alignment" truly requires:
- Ed showed us suffering can't be traded off
- Huang revealed constraints as innovation catalysts
- Cowen demonstrated growth as flourishing's engine
- Butler warned that any system without anti-capture armor will be corrupted
- Huerta centered the hands that feed us
- Reese exposed subsidy infrastructures that make exploitation profitable
- Havel reminded us conscience sanctuaries are non-negotiable
