- Views truth-telling and narrative repair as essential infrastructure
- Understands that alignment requires dismantling profitable systems of harm

The rewrite must feel inevitable - like these weren't additions but discoveries of what was missing all along. No more "pillars" that can be traded off; instead, interconnected boundaries where violating one collapses the whole.

Most importantly, this can't be another aspirational document. Every mechanism must answer: "Who would stop this from being gamed?" Because as Butler taught us, systems without teeth become trophies for the powerful.

Time to build something that doesn't just ask "are we aligned?" but "who gets to decide when we've failed?" - and makes sure that power can't be concentrated.
